
-- Home Brew

1. Get the home brew {This is onetime is the brew is not installed in your system}

/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

2. This will ask for "sudo" pin

Give network password

-- Install python

1. go to https://www.python.org/downloads/ and dowload 3.10.5
2. install it
3. check python3 --version
4. pip3 --version

-- Install Azure CLI

1. brew update && brew install azure-cli
2. if unable to find python or installed package

brew update && brew install python@3.10 && brew upgrade python@3.10
brew link --overwrite python@3.10

3. check if azure CLI got installed by typing:

az

-- Install Databricks CLI

1. brew install databricks-cli
2. Check if databricks CLI got installed by typing:

databricks

or

databricks --help